      <div xml:id="NA78-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaivu malintatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how [they] rejoice in the marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA78">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kōṭcuṟā vaḻaṅkum vāṭkē ḻiruṅkaḻi</l>
<l>            maṇiyēr neytaṉ māmalar niṟaiyap</l>
<l>            poṉṉēr nuṇṭātu puṉṉai tāam</l>
<l>            vīḻtāṭ ṭāḻaip pūkkamaḻ kāṉaṟ</l>
<l>            paṭarvantu naliyuñ cuṭarceṉ mālai </l>
<l>            nōymali paruvara ṉāmiva ṇuykaṅ</l>
<l>            kēṭṭiciṉ vāḻi tōḻi teṇkaḻi</l>
<l>            vaḷvā yāḻi yuḷvāy tōyiṉum</l>
<l>            puḷḷunimirn taṉṉa polampaṭaik kalimā</l>
<l>            valavaṉ kōluṟa vaṟiyā </l>
<l>            vuravunīrc cērppaṉ ṟērmaṇik kuralē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>We will escape suffering here, with increasing pain,</l>
<l rend="indent">at evening when the glow goes, when affliction comes [and] assaults [us]</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the seashore grove fragrant with flowers of the Tāḻai tree, aerial roots</l>
<l rend="indent3">down to [its] foot, where the Puṉṉai tree spreads gold-like fine pollen,</l>
<l rend="indent4">while the big blossoms of the sapphire-like waterlilies fill</l>
<l rend="indent4">the big backwaters full of light, where killing sharks roam.</l>
<l>Listen, oh friend:</l>
<l rend="indent">the voice of the chariot bells of the man from the coast of strong waters,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[his] proud horses with golden harness<note place="foot">For <term xml:lang="ta">poṉ paṭai</term> see note on NA 361.3.</note>, stretching out like birds,</l>
<l rend="indent3">not knowing of getting the stick by the charioteer,</l>
<l rend="indent3">even when the inner parts<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uḷvāy</term>: the <term xml:lang="ta">vāy</term> is here explained by T.V.G. alternatively as a locative suffix or as the nave of the wheel, the point being that the wheels of the chariot are submerged in the waters for a good part, but this still does not impede the speed of the horses.</note> of the sharp-mouthed wheels touch</l>
<l rend="indent4">the clear backwaters.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
